{"questionId":"d7afa874-519b-4f1b-b45f-1c75ea45613b_21","correctAnswer":"A","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Use the factored form","content":"Since the parabola has roots $10$ and $-5$, $f(x)=a(x-10)(x-(-5))$ for integer $a>1$."},{"title":"Expand to find $a+b$","content":"Expanding gives $f(x)=ax^2-a(10+(-5))x+a(10)(-5)$, so $b=-a(5)$ and $$a+b=a(1-(5))=-4a.$$"},{"title":"Pick a valid $a$","content":"With $a=2$ (integer $>1$), $a+b=-4\\cdot2=-8$. The answer is <strong>A</strong>."}]}